M&S Plans 600 Million-Pound Store Revamp, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 
2011-09-11T07:12:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/m-s-plans-600-million-pound-store-revamp-sunday-times-says.html
Marks & Spencer Group Plc (MKS)  will
start an overhaul of its stores costing 600 million pounds ($953
million) over three years, the Sunday Times reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Chief Executive Officer Mark Bolland will announce details
of the revamp tomorrow, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jonathan Browning  in  London  
 jbrowning9@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  